WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:05.797
<i>[rock music]</i>

00:05.880 --> 00:06.881
<i>kids:</i>
<i>Pig!</i>

00:06.965 --> 00:10.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:10.176 --> 00:10.552
<i>Goat!</i>

00:10.635 --> 00:13.471
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:13.555 --> 00:14.806
<i>Banana!</i>

00:14.889 --> 00:19.477
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:19.561 --> 00:20.770
<i>Cricket!</i>

00:20.854 --> 00:28.153
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:33.533 --> 00:35.160
- A-a-a-achoo!

00:35.243 --> 00:38.413
<i>all:</i>
<i>Pig! Goat! Banana! Cricket!</i>

00:41.875 --> 00:49.883
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:53.052 --> 00:54.471
{\an3}- Ahem.
Hi, everybody.

00:54.554 --> 00:58.057
{\an3}I wrote a song about how much
I hate shopping malls,

00:58.141 --> 00:59.976
and it goes a little
something like this.

01:00.059 --> 01:01.186
[inhales sharply]

01:01.269 --> 01:03.688
[jackhammer rumbles]

01:03.772 --> 01:04.855
{\an3}[whimpers]

01:04.938 --> 01:05.982
[jackhammer rumbles]

01:06.065 --> 01:07.484
- Ah!

01:07.567 --> 01:09.152
Aw, nuts.

01:09.235 --> 01:10.862
- W-what's going on?

01:10.945 --> 01:12.989
- They're cutting down
all the trees

01:13.072 --> 01:14.324
and building something

01:14.407 --> 01:16.785
enormously bigger
than all the trees.

01:18.453 --> 01:20.079
[machines rumbling
and whirring]

01:20.163 --> 01:21.831
<i>[mellow jazz music]</i>

01:21.915 --> 01:25.043
- This shopping mall is...

01:25.126 --> 01:26.461
{\an3}amazing!

01:26.544 --> 01:27.962
- But you just wrote a song

01:28.046 --> 01:30.006
{\an1}about how much you hate
shopping malls.

01:30.089 --> 01:31.341
{\an3}- Really?
[giggles]

01:31.424 --> 01:33.092
Doesn't sound like
something I'd do.

01:33.176 --> 01:34.177
{\an1}- But--

01:34.260 --> 01:35.470
- Do you really want
to go there?

01:35.553 --> 01:36.930
all:
Pig, Goat, Banana, Cricket

01:37.013 --> 01:38.264
living in a mall is awesome!

01:38.348 --> 01:39.641
High five!

01:41.434 --> 01:44.479
Maggot Burger--
who would wanna eat there?

01:44.562 --> 01:46.105
What else is around here?

01:46.189 --> 01:48.525
[glue glugging]

01:48.608 --> 01:49.609
Oh, man!

01:49.692 --> 01:51.194
They've got
a Gluezy Woozies here!

01:51.277 --> 01:56.741
My one-stop shop
for all my gluey needs.

01:56.825 --> 02:01.454
Oh, this is the best shooting
glue pistol on the market!

02:01.538 --> 02:04.707
Mama like!
[laughs]

02:04.791 --> 02:06.084
[glue spurts]

02:06.167 --> 02:09.963
- Ah!
[quacks]

02:10.045 --> 02:11.881
- [laughs]

02:11.965 --> 02:13.216
Huh?

02:13.299 --> 02:15.718
Ooh, bigger glue gun!

02:15.802 --> 02:17.804
Mama really like!

02:17.887 --> 02:18.847
[explosion]
Oof!

02:18.930 --> 02:19.848
[lips smacking]

02:19.931 --> 02:21.933
[glue splats]

02:22.016 --> 02:23.893
[muffled muttering]

02:23.977 --> 02:25.895
[laughs]

02:25.979 --> 02:27.981
Bull's-eye!

02:28.064 --> 02:31.651
Excuse me, is this the biggest
Gluezooka you got?

02:31.734 --> 02:33.778
- No, that is.

02:33.862 --> 02:36.155
<i>[angelic music]</i>

02:36.239 --> 02:40.827
Sweet mama's monkeys!

02:40.910 --> 02:44.414
That is the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen in my life.

02:44.497 --> 02:46.499
I got to have it!

02:46.583 --> 02:47.792
[grunts]

02:47.876 --> 02:49.961
Let's see how much
this baby costs.

02:50.044 --> 02:51.170
Ten hundred

02:51.254 --> 02:52.505
thousand million

02:52.589 --> 02:55.508
glutillion--
whatever comes after that!

02:55.592 --> 02:58.553
[gulps]
But I want it!

02:58.636 --> 03:01.639
{\an8}Oh, how am I gonna make
a ton of dough really quick?

03:03.391 --> 03:04.851
<i>[lively music]</i>

03:04.934 --> 03:08.938
Welcome to Banana's House
of Expensive Bargains!

03:09.022 --> 03:12.775
I'm Banana, nothing
in this house is not for sale.

03:12.859 --> 03:14.777
[crowd muttering]
Agh!

03:14.861 --> 03:17.113
[whimpers]

03:17.196 --> 03:19.282
<i>We got everything</i>
<i>you never thought you wanted</i>

03:19.365 --> 03:22.827
<i>but now realize</i>
<i>you can't live without.</i>

03:22.911 --> 03:25.079
[indistinct chattering]

03:25.163 --> 03:28.041
- Hmm...

03:28.124 --> 03:30.293
This complicated
scientific device

03:30.376 --> 03:32.378
fits my nose perfectly!

03:32.462 --> 03:34.088
How much?

03:34.172 --> 03:36.799
{\an8}- Mm, Cricket's most prized
possession, uh...

03:36.883 --> 03:37.842
{\an8}He won't miss it.

03:37.926 --> 03:38.927
{\an3}50 bucks.

03:39.010 --> 03:40.053
- Make it 10¢.

03:40.136 --> 03:42.555
{\an3}- Sold!
Greg, ring him up.

03:42.639 --> 03:44.307
Armpit Willy!

03:44.390 --> 03:46.976
{\an3}- Pits that don't quit.
Bushy-bushy.

03:47.060 --> 03:49.395
{\an3}How much for Goat's diary,
Banana man?

03:49.479 --> 03:52.148
{\an1}- 10 bucks, and I underlined
the good stuff for you,

03:52.231 --> 03:53.608
general scandals in red,

03:53.691 --> 03:56.361
{\an1}and bodily function mishaps
in green.

03:56.444 --> 03:57.987
- Juicy, juicy.

03:58.071 --> 04:00.156
[humming softly]

04:00.239 --> 04:01.366
[splat]

04:01.449 --> 04:03.326
- Gregs, let's speed
this thing up.

04:03.409 --> 04:04.035
Mark everything half off!

04:04.118 --> 04:06.663
<i>[cash register dings]</i>

04:06.746 --> 04:12.752
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:12.835 --> 04:14.796
Whoo!

04:14.879 --> 04:17.339
{\an1}- Wow,
this "Space Gnome" costume

04:17.423 --> 04:18.632
is awesome.

04:18.716 --> 04:20.093
Is it for sale?

04:20.176 --> 04:21.719
{\an3}- That's your
"Space Gnome" costume.

04:21.803 --> 04:23.179
- I know.
How much is it?

04:23.262 --> 04:26.474
- It's 100 bucks!
- I'll take it!

04:26.557 --> 04:28.476
- Hey, where did you get
that cash anyway?

04:28.559 --> 04:32.355
{\an1}- Your wallet.
[chuckles]

04:32.438 --> 04:35.316
- [snores]

04:41.447 --> 04:42.782
- Boy, you guys look tired.

04:42.865 --> 04:44.325
I have just the thing for you.

04:44.409 --> 04:46.411
Welcome to
Banana's Nap Station,

04:46.494 --> 04:48.454
only 8¢ for the first minute,

04:48.538 --> 04:50.748
40 bucks for each
additional minute.

04:50.832 --> 04:52.250
[coins jingling]

04:52.333 --> 04:53.751
[critters squeaking
and muttering]

04:53.835 --> 04:55.086
[glass shatters]

04:55.169 --> 04:57.046
{\an1}Hey, hey, hey!
You break it, you bought it!

04:57.130 --> 05:00.258
- [snores]

05:00.341 --> 05:03.469
{\an3}- Ooh, look at that
nasty throw rug.

05:03.553 --> 05:05.096
{\an1}- Hey, Nasty Cat,
what's up?

05:05.179 --> 05:09.350
{\an3}- Keepin' it nasty,
as nasty as I want to be.

05:09.434 --> 05:11.269
{\an3}I want that.
Do you gift wrap?

05:11.352 --> 05:13.604
- Sure.

05:13.688 --> 05:15.773
- [muffled shouting]

05:18.818 --> 05:19.986
- [slurping]

05:20.069 --> 05:22.697
- Good news, Banana,
we sold everything!

05:22.780 --> 05:24.741
- Sweet mama's moneys!

05:24.824 --> 05:26.159
You know what that means,
right?

05:26.242 --> 05:29.996
[crashing,
crowd screaming]

05:30.079 --> 05:31.789
Whee! Let the fun begin!

05:31.873 --> 05:35.001
Who am I gonna blast first
with my Gluezooka?

05:35.084 --> 05:37.211
<i>[militaristic trumpet music]</i>

05:37.295 --> 05:39.380
- [quacks]
- Been there.

05:39.464 --> 05:41.174
[muffled muttering]
Done that.

05:41.257 --> 05:43.551
Fresh meat.
- [whimpers]

05:43.634 --> 05:45.219
- Hold up, that's Goat!

05:46.846 --> 05:48.639
{\an1}Goat, what's with
the gift wrap?

05:48.723 --> 05:51.059
- [muffled speech]

05:51.142 --> 05:52.351
- How dare you talk
to my merchandise?

05:52.435 --> 05:54.896
{\an1}- But she's not
your merchandise.

05:54.979 --> 05:56.272
She's my merchandise.

05:56.355 --> 05:57.940
- [muffled shouting]

05:58.024 --> 05:59.776
{\an1}- Besides,
Goat wasn't for sale.

05:59.859 --> 06:00.735
{\an1}[grunts]

06:00.818 --> 06:02.070
- Uh, excuse me?

06:02.153 --> 06:04.113
{\an3}You said
nothing's not for sale.

06:04.197 --> 06:05.656
Good day to you.

06:05.740 --> 06:08.701
- But--but without her,
who's gonna cut my toenails...

06:08.785 --> 06:10.203
<i>[fart sounds]</i>

06:10.286 --> 06:12.288
And milk my cow?

06:12.371 --> 06:14.332
- Somebody's gotta do it.

06:14.415 --> 06:15.541
{\an3}[cries]

06:17.502 --> 06:18.586
- Listen, Nasty Cat,

06:18.669 --> 06:19.295
how about I give you

06:19.378 --> 06:22.298
all these beautiful Gregs

06:22.381 --> 06:26.135
{\an1}in exchange for that
boring, silly, lame Goat.

06:26.219 --> 06:27.553
- Escape.

06:27.637 --> 06:30.473
{\an3}- No way.
Goats are way nastier.

06:30.556 --> 06:33.643
{\an3}She's going to go great
with my lime green blouse.

06:33.726 --> 06:35.645
{\an1}- Then let me
sweeten the deal.

06:35.728 --> 06:39.482
{\an1}[stammers]
I'll throw in...

06:39.565 --> 06:40.566
Me.

06:40.650 --> 06:41.818
- I don't want any of you.

06:41.901 --> 06:43.444
You ain't nasty enough.

06:43.528 --> 06:45.071
- I'm plenty nasty!

06:45.154 --> 06:47.740
Come on, Nasty Cat,
you're a savvy businesswoman.

06:47.824 --> 06:50.201
There's got to be something
I could trade for Goat.

06:50.284 --> 06:51.410
{\an3}- Hmm...

06:51.494 --> 06:54.497
{\an3}What about that
nasty little number?

06:54.580 --> 06:56.457
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:56.541 --> 06:59.418
- Uh...
that's my Gluezooka,

06:59.502 --> 07:01.879
my most prized possession.

07:01.963 --> 07:03.464
Oh, I just got it!

07:03.548 --> 07:05.341
- Well, forget it, then,
no deal.

07:05.424 --> 07:07.510
{\an1}- Fine, 'cause there's
absolutely no way

07:07.593 --> 07:10.555
you're getting your
grimy mitts on my--

07:10.638 --> 07:11.347
- [whimpers]

07:11.430 --> 07:14.559
<i>[sad instrumental music]</i>

07:14.642 --> 07:15.810
- All right.

07:17.395 --> 07:19.522
Good-bye, my only true love.

07:19.605 --> 07:22.567
[lips smack]

07:22.650 --> 07:23.860
You take the tank.

07:23.943 --> 07:24.944
I'll take the goat,

07:25.027 --> 07:27.029
but this is by far
the hardest choice

07:27.113 --> 07:28.656
{\an1}I've ever made
in my life.

07:28.739 --> 07:31.534
- That's the hardest choice
you've ever made?

07:31.617 --> 07:33.911
Why,
you flang flung glurmus--

07:33.995 --> 07:35.872
- No need to thank me.

07:35.955 --> 07:37.206
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:37.290 --> 07:38.749
[alarm blares]

07:38.833 --> 07:42.628
- Whoa, you're too nasty!

07:42.712 --> 07:46.132
- Too nasty!

07:46.215 --> 07:48.801
- Tanky, you do care!

07:48.885 --> 07:50.553
- You're the one I love,
Banany.

07:50.636 --> 07:53.264
Why are you afraid
of commitment?

07:53.347 --> 07:54.682
[lips smack]

07:54.765 --> 07:56.559
- Oh, oh, oh, okay!
Okay, that's plenty!

07:56.642 --> 07:59.687
No, seriously, okay, stop!
Wah!

08:02.732 --> 08:06.068
- Ah, the perfect spot
to launch my new business

08:06.152 --> 08:08.571
and fulfill my lifelong dream
of operating

08:08.654 --> 08:11.449
my very own wizarding kiosk.

08:11.532 --> 08:12.491
- Hello, Goat.

08:12.575 --> 08:14.410
- Thomas Jefferson.

08:14.493 --> 08:16.579
{\an3}You have
a wizarding kiosk too?

08:16.662 --> 08:18.539
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:18.623 --> 08:19.874
- That's right, fuzz lumps.

08:19.957 --> 08:22.501
The best wizarding kiosk
in the whole mall.

08:22.585 --> 08:23.586
[laughs]

08:23.669 --> 08:25.087
[eagle screeches]

08:25.171 --> 08:27.256
{\an3}- Ha-ha!
We'll see about that!

08:27.340 --> 08:29.133
{\an3}Oh, boy!
My first customer.

08:29.217 --> 08:30.509
Hey, Armpit Willy.

08:30.593 --> 08:32.761
{\an1}- Hey, Goat,
I was just reading your diary.

08:32.845 --> 08:34.138
Did that rash ever go away?

08:34.222 --> 08:35.640
{\an3}- Ah!
Give me that!

08:35.722 --> 08:37.183
And, yes, it did,

08:37.265 --> 08:39.477
{\an3}eventually.

08:39.559 --> 08:41.770
Can I interest you
in a crystal ball?

08:41.854 --> 08:44.815
You can see your future.

08:44.899 --> 08:46.108
<i>[mystical tones]</i>

08:46.192 --> 08:49.278
{\an1}- Ooh, it's my tombstone.
Ooh...

08:49.362 --> 08:51.948
{\an1}But look, someone's there,
crying for me.

08:52.031 --> 08:53.908
<i>It's you, Goat, you care!</i>

08:53.991 --> 08:55.534
[video game music]

08:55.618 --> 08:57.662
<i>No, it's just you</i>
<i>playing a game on your phone.</i>

08:57.745 --> 08:59.497
No one cares.

08:59.580 --> 09:00.873
- How's that?

09:00.957 --> 09:03.459
{\an3}- You want a crystal ball?
I got one for you.

09:03.543 --> 09:06.587
{\an3}Check out this radical future,
broheim.

09:06.671 --> 09:07.755
<i>[rock music]</i>

09:07.838 --> 09:10.675
- All right, I like it!

09:10.758 --> 09:12.885
I'll take it, my man.

09:12.969 --> 09:14.679
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

09:14.762 --> 09:16.138
- [spluttering]

09:16.222 --> 09:18.766
No good Thomas Jefferson
stealing my customers!

09:18.849 --> 09:20.184
Fling flang flarget fun fliggit!

09:20.268 --> 09:21.310
[crystal ball shatters]

09:21.394 --> 09:22.687
[growls]

09:22.770 --> 09:25.356
{\an3}Hey, Tiny Goosey,
wand shopping?

09:25.439 --> 09:27.942
{\an3}'Cause I just happen to have
the perfect wand for you.

09:28.025 --> 09:31.821
{\an3}Allow me to demonstrate.
Abra-ka-abs!

09:31.904 --> 09:34.907
- Five-pack abs...
Where's the sixth?

09:34.991 --> 09:36.325
You hate me.
[cries]

09:36.409 --> 09:38.369
- No, I wuv you.

09:38.452 --> 09:40.121
{\an3}This is just
the five-pack ab wand.

09:40.204 --> 09:42.999
{\an3}I'll order you the six-pack ab
wand right now.

09:43.082 --> 09:44.542
{\an1}- Why wait around,
Tiny Goosey?

09:44.625 --> 09:47.295
{\an1}I have all of your
ab wand needs in stock

09:47.378 --> 09:49.839
{\an1}at my White House
Warlock Wagon today.

09:49.922 --> 09:51.215
[eagle screeches]

09:51.299 --> 09:53.259
[whooshing]

09:53.342 --> 09:55.011
[bang]

09:55.094 --> 09:57.388
- Oh, my!
I wuv 'em!

09:57.471 --> 09:58.681
[growls]

09:58.764 --> 10:01.017
{\an9}And I wuv that wand,
and I wuv you.

10:01.100 --> 10:02.560
{\an8}I'll take it!

10:02.643 --> 10:04.729
{\an3}- B-b-but you're ruining
my dream of running

10:04.812 --> 10:06.063
a successful wizarding kiosk.

10:06.147 --> 10:09.025
Abra-ka-abs!

10:09.108 --> 10:12.028
{\an1}- She's blinded me
with face abs!

10:12.111 --> 10:13.195
[crashing]

10:13.279 --> 10:14.739
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:14.822 --> 10:16.115
Good gracious!

10:16.198 --> 10:18.075
{\an3}- Oops, I guess
that settles who has

10:18.159 --> 10:22.371
{\an3}the better wizarding merch
once and for all, Jefferson.

10:22.455 --> 10:23.789
Yo, yo, lizard gizzard.

10:23.873 --> 10:24.457
I'm open for wiz-ness.

10:24.540 --> 10:26.709
{\an3}Get it?
[laughs]

10:26.792 --> 10:27.668
I'm also a word wizard.

10:27.752 --> 10:30.046
- And I'm also
Thomas Jefferson

10:30.129 --> 10:31.756
in an awesome
lizard disguise...

10:31.839 --> 10:33.215
you can buy at my kiosk
half off.

10:33.299 --> 10:35.509
Fist-a-kazoo!

10:36.469 --> 10:39.388
- Ow! Ow! No more punch!

10:39.472 --> 10:41.557
{\an3}What are you doing?
Stop punch--

10:41.640 --> 10:43.684
- As my old friend Washington
said,

10:43.768 --> 10:44.894
"I cannot tell a lie."

10:44.977 --> 10:46.520
I made you punch your face.

10:48.647 --> 10:50.024
- Fist-a-kazam!

10:50.107 --> 10:51.609
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:51.692 --> 10:53.319
Welcome to Punchachusetts!

10:53.402 --> 10:55.529
Population: you.

10:55.613 --> 10:56.697
[eagle screeches]

10:56.781 --> 10:58.282
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:58.366 --> 11:00.576
- [muffled moaning]

11:00.659 --> 11:03.079
- Now, that's what I call
a real "Whig" party.

11:03.162 --> 11:06.165
Hilarious and historically
accurate, ha-ha.

11:06.248 --> 11:09.502
{\an1}- I'll impeach you
from the mall.

11:09.585 --> 11:11.253
- You'll have to catch me first.

11:11.337 --> 11:14.632
Zoombroom 5000, away!

11:14.715 --> 11:16.342
- Come back here, Goat!

11:19.095 --> 11:21.222
- Ha!

11:21.305 --> 11:22.973
Ha-ha!
- Whoa!

11:23.057 --> 11:25.434
- Have at thee!

11:25.518 --> 11:27.228
- Whoa!
Missed me! Ha-ha!

11:27.311 --> 11:29.021
[bell rings]

11:29.105 --> 11:31.357
You can't get me, Jefferson!

11:31.440 --> 11:33.109
- Hey! Ho!

11:33.192 --> 11:34.777
- Ah!

11:34.860 --> 11:36.529
{\an1}- Whoops!
Sorry!

11:36.612 --> 11:37.780
- [whimpers]

11:37.863 --> 11:40.866
{\an1}- Look what you made me do,
Jefferson.

11:42.535 --> 11:43.911
Hi, Cricket.

11:43.994 --> 11:45.121
- Hi, Goat.
What's up?

11:45.204 --> 11:46.372
- Just a psycho president

11:46.455 --> 11:47.957
{\an1}is trying to annihilate me
is all.

11:48.040 --> 11:49.375
{\an1}Other than that,
I'm dandy.

11:49.458 --> 11:50.751
- Oh, that's nice.

11:50.835 --> 11:51.919
- Hiyah!
- [grunts]

11:55.923 --> 11:59.677
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

11:59.760 --> 12:01.637
- [groans]

12:01.721 --> 12:04.974
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:05.057 --> 12:07.893
{\an3}Welcome to
the Jortsatorium.

12:07.977 --> 12:10.312
The world's only
jort superstore,

12:10.396 --> 12:12.022
for all your jorts needs.

12:12.106 --> 12:13.482
- What's a jorts?

12:13.566 --> 12:16.569
- You see, when a pair of jeans
loves a pair of shorts,

12:16.652 --> 12:17.987
they make jorts.

12:18.070 --> 12:20.990
- I always wondered
where they came from.

12:21.073 --> 12:22.199
- Wanna try on a pair?

12:22.283 --> 12:24.243
- Sorry, not my thing.
See ya.

12:24.326 --> 12:25.661
- I get it.

12:25.744 --> 12:27.830
You're not cool enough
to wear jorts.

12:27.913 --> 12:29.498
- What?
I'm plenty cool.

12:29.582 --> 12:31.333
Give me them jorts.

12:31.417 --> 12:33.002
- Hmm-hmm!

12:35.004 --> 12:36.630
[cackles]

12:36.714 --> 12:39.383
- [grunts]
They're not coming off!

12:39.467 --> 12:40.634
{\an3}- You fool!

12:40.718 --> 12:43.053
I've been stuck
for 3,000 years

12:43.137 --> 12:44.930
in the Jortsatorium,

12:45.014 --> 12:48.142
and now I'm finally free!

12:48.225 --> 12:49.518
- W-what's happening?

12:49.602 --> 12:50.936
- [cackles]

12:51.020 --> 12:52.188
Until you get someone

12:52.271 --> 12:54.523
to try on a pair
of these stinkin' jorts,

12:54.607 --> 12:56.942
you're trapped in here
forever.

12:57.026 --> 12:58.402
[laughs]

12:58.486 --> 13:01.197
[thudding]

13:01.280 --> 13:02.907
[cackles]

13:02.990 --> 13:04.408
- [groans]

13:04.492 --> 13:06.827
- [cackling]

13:06.911 --> 13:08.662
- But I don't want
to spend my whole life

13:08.746 --> 13:10.039
in the Jortsatorium.

13:10.122 --> 13:11.457
I'll never see my lab again.

13:11.540 --> 13:13.459
I'll never see my friends again.

13:13.542 --> 13:14.710
[gasps]

13:14.793 --> 13:16.670
I'll never see Goat again!

13:16.754 --> 13:19.507
I need to find a customer
and put some jorts on 'em.

13:19.590 --> 13:21.133
Ooh, here comes one now.

13:21.217 --> 13:23.260
Hello, young sir.

13:23.344 --> 13:25.012
My thorapic ongometer!

13:25.095 --> 13:27.431
Give me that!

13:27.515 --> 13:29.016
I hit myself.

13:29.099 --> 13:33.020
{\an3}Now, can I interest you
in some jorts this fine day?

13:33.103 --> 13:35.064
- I'm just looking
for the outhouse.

13:35.147 --> 13:36.440
- I'll tell you where it is

13:36.524 --> 13:38.359
if you try on a pair
of exquisite jorts.

13:38.442 --> 13:41.403
{\an1}- And be trapped in the
Jortsatorium for all eternity?

13:41.487 --> 13:42.738
No, thank you.

13:42.821 --> 13:44.156
- No, wait--

13:44.240 --> 13:46.951
[glass thuds]
Oh!

13:47.034 --> 13:48.410
Curse you, jorts!

13:48.494 --> 13:50.246
I'll never get someone
to try them on!

13:50.329 --> 13:52.081
They're too dang ugly!

13:52.164 --> 13:53.332
- [chomping]

13:53.415 --> 13:55.543
♪ Onions, onions,
me loves onions ♪

13:55.626 --> 13:57.920
♪ Onions, onions,
me got onions ♪

13:58.003 --> 14:00.089
♪ Bulb and peels
and layers of onions ♪

14:00.172 --> 14:02.174
♪ Brings a tear to my eye ♪

14:02.258 --> 14:03.467
♪ Onions, onions... ♪

14:03.551 --> 14:06.303
- The president of the planet.
[laughs]

14:06.387 --> 14:10.432
Soon to be the president
of the Jortsatorium.

14:10.516 --> 14:11.934
- [burps]

14:12.017 --> 14:13.602
{\an1}- Hey, Mr. President
of the Planet,

14:13.686 --> 14:15.020
your breath stanks.

14:15.104 --> 14:17.731
How about a piece of gum?

14:17.815 --> 14:20.818
- A piece of gum,
oh, goody!

14:20.901 --> 14:23.946
[hums]

14:24.029 --> 14:24.947
Huh?

14:25.030 --> 14:26.824
- I did it!
I'm free!

14:26.907 --> 14:29.451
[balloon inflating]

14:29.535 --> 14:30.369
[wind whistles]

14:30.452 --> 14:31.704
What?
Where are you going?

14:31.787 --> 14:33.872
Come back here,
you onion lover!

14:33.956 --> 14:36.125
- Thanks for the gum,
Citizen Cricket.

14:36.208 --> 14:40.462
[singing indistinctly]

14:40.546 --> 14:42.131
- Oh, now what?

14:42.214 --> 14:45.801
Wh-wh-wh-wh-who
am I gonna get to wear jorts?

14:45.884 --> 14:47.428
Wh-wh-who?

14:47.511 --> 14:48.721
{\an3}Oh!

14:48.804 --> 14:50.306
- [hooting]

14:50.389 --> 14:52.141
- If I shoot
this owl-woman-lady

14:52.224 --> 14:54.435
with a temporary paralysis ray

14:54.518 --> 14:55.978
from my thorapic ongometer,

14:56.061 --> 14:58.230
I'll be able to slip her
into a pair of jorts

14:58.314 --> 15:00.691
and then get out of this mess.

15:00.774 --> 15:03.319
[laser buzzes]

15:03.402 --> 15:06.655
[electricity buzzes]

15:06.739 --> 15:08.115
- [hoots]

15:08.198 --> 15:11.243
My, what an usual
piece of modern furniture.

15:11.327 --> 15:14.622
{\an1}Just the place
to rest my ample rump.

15:14.705 --> 15:16.999
- [whimpers]

15:17.082 --> 15:19.001
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:19.084 --> 15:22.046
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:22.129 --> 15:23.005
Oh!

15:23.088 --> 15:24.923
- What a piece of cheap junk.

15:26.800 --> 15:28.177
- [sobbing]

15:28.260 --> 15:30.554
I'm never gonna
get out of here.

15:30.638 --> 15:32.473
[glass thudding]

15:36.143 --> 15:39.480
- "Space Gnomes Part 3"
in 3-D?

15:39.563 --> 15:41.357
That's my favorite!

15:41.440 --> 15:42.775
[alarm buzzes]
Sold out?

15:42.858 --> 15:46.528
I'll just wait
for the next screening.

15:46.612 --> 15:48.697
[alarm buzzes]

15:48.781 --> 15:50.199
Sold out forever?

15:50.282 --> 15:52.826
But I've got my official
Emperor Merkel Space Gnomes

15:52.910 --> 15:54.995
costume on and everything!

15:55.079 --> 15:57.414
This is giving me
a tummy ache.

15:57.498 --> 15:58.666
[groans]

15:58.749 --> 15:59.667
[farts]

15:59.750 --> 16:00.709
- Hello, Pig.

16:00.793 --> 16:02.044
- Arnold Fartzenegger,

16:02.127 --> 16:03.629
what do you think I should do?

16:03.712 --> 16:05.631
- Why don't you sneak
into the movie, Pig?

16:05.714 --> 16:07.383
- But that would be wrong.

16:07.466 --> 16:10.094
{\an1}- "That would be wr--"
Don't be a wimp your whole life.

16:10.177 --> 16:11.387
All right, get in there,

16:11.470 --> 16:14.306
{\an1}and see the heck
out of that movie.

16:14.390 --> 16:17.309
- What are you doing?
We've got work to do.

16:17.393 --> 16:19.061
- But I don't work here.

16:19.144 --> 16:21.063
- I want a popcorn.

16:21.146 --> 16:24.316
{\an3}- Popcorn?
What size?

16:24.400 --> 16:26.735
{\an1}- Well, the fun tub,
of course.

16:26.819 --> 16:28.237
{\an3}- Got it.

16:28.320 --> 16:29.905
[groans]

16:33.784 --> 16:35.452
- Oh, how dare you?

16:35.536 --> 16:38.122
I demand to see the manager.

16:38.205 --> 16:40.040
{\an1}- Where's
my extra large soda?

16:40.124 --> 16:41.417
- Soda--got it.

16:41.500 --> 16:42.835
[butter glugs]

16:42.918 --> 16:44.211
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

16:45.504 --> 16:46.505
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:46.588 --> 16:48.382
- [gulps and screams]

16:48.465 --> 16:49.633
This isn't soda!

16:49.717 --> 16:51.260
It's hot liquid butter!

16:51.343 --> 16:52.594
- Whoopsie-dingles...

16:54.346 --> 16:55.931
[splattering and sizzling]

16:56.014 --> 16:58.517
- Hoooo...

16:58.600 --> 17:01.270
Oh, my beak!

17:01.353 --> 17:03.897
{\an3}- Hey, you!
You don't work here.

17:03.981 --> 17:05.941
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

17:06.023 --> 17:07.276
- Pig, run!

17:07.358 --> 17:09.653
Go and see that gnome movie
that you love.

17:09.737 --> 17:12.406
{\an1}- Thanks,
Arnold Fartzenegger.

17:12.489 --> 17:14.074
- Come back here.

17:14.157 --> 17:19.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:20.079 --> 17:22.207
- Finally, now I can
watch the movie

17:22.290 --> 17:25.627
with the best seat
in the house.

17:25.711 --> 17:27.628
[projector whirs]

17:27.713 --> 17:30.382
It's happening!
It's happening!

17:30.466 --> 17:32.050
<i>[vibrant music]</i>

17:32.134 --> 17:33.719
<i>- [cackles]</i>

17:33.802 --> 17:36.847
<i>I'm going to get you,</i>
<i>Space Gnomes!</i>

17:36.930 --> 17:40.225
{\an3}- Pardon me, excuse me,
pardon me, excuse me.

17:40.309 --> 17:41.769
{\an1}[farting]

17:41.852 --> 17:45.189
- [giggling]

17:45.272 --> 17:46.607
<i>- [gargling laughter]</i>

17:46.690 --> 17:49.193
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:49.276 --> 17:51.487
- Boo, Lord Gargle Mouth!

17:51.570 --> 17:55.240
The Space Gnomes are going
to kick your evil space booty.

17:55.324 --> 17:57.076
This time, for good.

17:57.159 --> 17:58.410
Yowchies!

17:58.494 --> 18:00.662
Ah!

18:00.746 --> 18:04.750
[thudding and screaming]

18:04.833 --> 18:08.337
<i>Hey, everybody,</i>
<i>I'm a Space Gnome in 3-D.</i>

18:08.420 --> 18:09.963
- Boo!
- Hey!

18:10.047 --> 18:11.423
- Boo!

18:11.507 --> 18:14.218
<i>- I mean, hold up a sec.</i>
<i>I'll fix it.</i>

18:14.301 --> 18:16.637
<i>Stop booing.</i>

18:16.720 --> 18:17.846
- You dunderhead!

18:17.930 --> 18:20.641
{\an3}You broke the projector
and ruined the movie.

18:20.724 --> 18:24.645
- But all I wanted to do
was to see the Space Gnomes

18:24.728 --> 18:27.856
defeat Lord Gargle Mouth.

18:27.940 --> 18:29.691
[gasps]
What's going on?

18:29.775 --> 18:31.443
- The movie's back, yeah!

18:31.527 --> 18:33.028
- Whoa! Cool!

18:33.111 --> 18:36.198
- Awesome.

18:36.281 --> 18:38.116
- Nifty.

18:38.200 --> 18:39.701
- I won't be back!

18:39.785 --> 18:42.037
- [cries]

18:42.120 --> 18:45.791
- ♪ Popcorn, popcorn,
me love popcorn ♪

18:45.874 --> 18:47.751
[crowd cheering]

18:47.835 --> 18:52.214
- [gargling, groaning]

18:52.297 --> 18:54.341
[squawking]

18:54.424 --> 18:57.845
- This 3-D feels so real!

18:57.928 --> 18:59.388
- Oh!

18:59.471 --> 19:02.266
It feels like he's really
kicking me in the fun tub.

19:02.349 --> 19:06.061
Wait, he is kicking me
in the fun tub!

19:06.144 --> 19:08.063
- [clucks]

19:08.146 --> 19:09.273
- Oh!

19:09.356 --> 19:10.566
[crowd screaming]

19:10.649 --> 19:12.776
- He's so bad!
I love it.

19:12.860 --> 19:13.986
I mean, I hate it.

19:14.069 --> 19:16.405
I mean, I love
to love hating it.

19:16.488 --> 19:18.282
- [clucks]

19:18.365 --> 19:21.702
{\an1}Emperor Merkel,
leader of the Space Gnomes.

19:22.911 --> 19:24.621
- Uh... yeah.

19:24.705 --> 19:28.000
{\an1}- You have always been
my greatest enemy.

19:28.083 --> 19:29.585
- [gasps]
How's that?

19:29.668 --> 19:30.794
What?

19:30.878 --> 19:33.380
- Prepare to be obliterated!

19:33.463 --> 19:36.717
[laser buzzes]

19:36.800 --> 19:40.721
Get back here,
Emperor Merkel.

19:40.804 --> 19:42.598
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:42.681 --> 19:45.225
Out of my way, Whig boy!

19:47.185 --> 19:50.772
- Oh...
Whoa!

19:50.856 --> 19:54.109
Oh!
Stars and stripes!

19:54.192 --> 19:56.653
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:56.737 --> 19:58.113
- Gotcha!

19:58.196 --> 19:59.197
<i>[triumphant music]</i>

19:59.281 --> 20:00.782
- Why'd you save me?

20:00.866 --> 20:03.952
{\an3}- United we stand,
divided we fall.

20:04.036 --> 20:05.287
- Speaking of falling...

20:05.370 --> 20:08.582
- Typical Jefferson!

20:08.665 --> 20:10.334
[groans]

20:10.417 --> 20:11.710
{\an1}- [quacks]

20:11.793 --> 20:13.754
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

20:13.837 --> 20:16.423
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:16.506 --> 20:17.883
- Hey, space slob!

20:17.966 --> 20:22.179
Say hello to
my really big friend!

20:22.262 --> 20:25.891
- That puny Earth squirt pistol
can't do anything

20:25.974 --> 20:28.602
to the mighty Lord--

20:28.685 --> 20:30.228
- Ha!

20:30.312 --> 20:32.356
- How am I ever gonna get
someone in their right mind

20:32.439 --> 20:35.567
into a pair of these horrible,
horrible jorts?

20:35.651 --> 20:39.237
- Wah!
[gargling]

20:39.321 --> 20:42.991
- Hello, can I interest you
in a pair of jorts?

20:43.075 --> 20:44.493
- Jorts?

20:44.576 --> 20:45.702
[together]
♪ Jorts, jorts ♪

20:45.786 --> 20:46.828
♪ Put them on ♪

20:46.912 --> 20:48.330
♪ You'd look great ♪

20:48.413 --> 20:49.706
♪ With them on ♪

20:49.790 --> 20:51.333
- Well, I wasn't planning
on shopping,

20:51.416 --> 20:54.127
but summer is right around
the corner.

20:54.211 --> 20:56.213
[wind whistles]

20:56.296 --> 20:59.007
[groans]

20:59.091 --> 21:02.260
A little snug in the fun zone.

21:02.344 --> 21:03.428
Oh, boy.

21:03.512 --> 21:06.515
[groans]

21:09.601 --> 21:10.519
Come on,
come on,

21:10.602 --> 21:11.812
this is my size.

21:11.895 --> 21:13.772
Come on, come on,
it's a 34.

21:13.855 --> 21:15.691
I've gotta squeeze into a 34.

21:15.774 --> 21:17.651
Ah, come on, come on, come on.

21:17.734 --> 21:20.404
It's this Italian cut,
it always...

21:20.487 --> 21:23.532
{\an1}[groans]
Ah, ah, yes--

21:23.615 --> 21:25.033
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

21:25.117 --> 21:26.034
[snap]

21:26.118 --> 21:28.745
{\an1}[grunting]

21:28.829 --> 21:30.914
{\an1}I think I'm in!
Ah.

21:30.998 --> 21:32.249
[thunder crashes]

21:32.332 --> 21:35.836
- Ha, yes!
I'm free!

21:35.919 --> 21:38.922
{\an3}Now you're the keeper
of the Jortsatorium

21:39.006 --> 21:41.383
{\an3}forever!

21:41.466 --> 21:43.010
- What?
What have you done to me?

21:43.093 --> 21:44.511
Get back here!

21:44.594 --> 21:45.595
[groans]

21:45.679 --> 21:47.472
[glass thuds]

21:47.556 --> 21:51.852
Jorts!

21:51.935 --> 21:53.228
- We did it!

21:53.311 --> 21:54.730
[together]
Pig, Goat, Banana, Cricket!

21:54.813 --> 21:57.065
Lord Gargle Mouth has to wear
jorts forever!

21:57.149 --> 21:58.817
High five!

21:58.900 --> 21:59.901
<i>Jorts!</i>

22:01.111 --> 22:05.115
{\an8}[gentle acoustic guitar music]

22:05.198 --> 22:13.206
{\an8}♪ ♪

22:25.135 --> 22:27.846
{\an8}[whoopee cushion whistles]
